Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved) into small pieces.

Add a little @oil{to taste} to a large #pot{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add half the onion. Fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @water{240%ml} and half the @vegetable stock{1/2%sachet} to the pot. Bring to the boil. Add the @bulgur wheat{120%grams}, bring back to the boil. Simmer, ~{1%minute}.

Cover the pot and remove from heat. Leave for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Trim the @courgette{1} then slice into 1cm thick rounds.

Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%pack}. Pop half into a #bowl{} and roughly mash with the back of a #fork{}.

Heat a pan on high heat (no oil).

When hot, add the courgette rounds and cook until charred, ~{3-4%minutes} each side. Turn only every couple of minutes - this will result in the courgette picking up some nice colour.

Once cooked, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}, then chop into roughly 1cm pieces. Transfer to a bowl and cover to keep warm.

Wipe out the (now empty) pan and return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

When hot, add the remaining onion and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the garlic and chickpeas (both whole and mashed) and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Pour in the @passata{1%pack}, @water{100%ml}, remaining @vegetable stock{1/2%sachet} and two-thirds of the @harissa paste{2/3%sachet}.

Stir together, then bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Bring to the boil, stir in the @prawns{180%grams} and cook for a further ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

When everything is ready, fluff up the bulgur using a fork and stir through the remaining @harissa paste{1/3%sachet} until well combined.

Share the bulgur between your bowls and top with the harissa prawn stew.

Finish with the charred courgette.